bcl:definition.bcl:text:
  certificate of completion means a certificate under section 7
stating that work under a contract or subcontract has been completed and includes an order
made under section 7 (5);

  completed, if used with reference to a contract or
subcontract in respect of an improvement, means substantially completed or performed, not
necessarily totally completed or performed;

  head contractor means a contractor who is engaged to do
substantially all of the work respecting an improvement, whether or not others are engaged
as subcontractors, material suppliers or workers;

  land title office means the land title office for the land
title district or districts in which the land or any part of it is located and on which
the improvement is made or is being made;

  notice of certification of completion means a notice in the
prescribed form stating that a certificate of completion or a court order to the same
effect has been issued;

work is done or material is supplied, and includes all persons claiming under the
          owner, but does not include a mortgagee unless the mortgagee is in possession of the
          land;
